  <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Marie Bobrowski, born Marie Krolikowski, lived on the West Side of Detroit, Mich., during World War II, worked for the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, and wrote to many soldiers.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection consists of a scrapbook, photo album, letters, military insignia, and miscellanea, mainly materials received from soldiers corresponding with Marie Krolikowski, but also newspaper and magazine clippings about war-related topics and cartoons relating to young women writing to soldiers. Correspondents include L.B. Adams, Stanley Krolikowski (a P.O.W., her letters to him were returned by the Japanese), Francis Laskowski, and Robbins (a postcard of war devastation in Manila). The collection also includes collected material relating to Dwight H. Johnson, Vietnam War Congressional Medal of Honor winner from Detroit, who was later killed in a robbery.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="506" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection is open for research use.</subfield>
  </datafield>
